news.title: China Vanke's property services arm Onewo to raise $783 million through IPO
news.para: The subsidiary, Onewo Space-Tech Service, has set a price range of HK$47.1 to HK$52.7 a piece in the public offering of 116.74 million of its shares, which represent 10% of the company's share capital, according to a deal term sheet.

news.title: Eris Lifesciences’ CMD buys luxury apartment in Mumbai's Worli for Rs 61 crore
news.para: Bakshi has purchased the apartment spread over a carpet area of 64,50 sq ft on the 46th floor of the project from the developer, Oberoi Realty’s subsidiary Oasis Realty, that is executing the project.

news.title: DB Realty's subsidiary looks to sell Mumbai land for Rs 480 crore
news.para: Only agreement for aale has not been been entered into. The proposed transaction is subject to customary diligence and necessary approvals and is expected to close within 60 to 90 days, it said.

news.title: Adani to become most profitable cement manufacturer
news.para: Stating reasons for the foray into the cement space, he said while India is the second largest producer of cement in the world, its per capita consumption is just 250 kg compared to 1,600 kg of China. "This is almost a 7x headroom for growth."

news.title: Ansal API under police lens for 'irregular' land deals in Panipat
news.para: The complaints have come from a group led by former district counsellor Jogender Swami, who alleged that the Ansal group and town planning department officials had connived in arranging the unlawful land deals.

news.title: Kanpur: KDA residency has no structural safety issues, say experts
news.para: ​​Rohit Khanna chief engineer KDA in a release stated that residents of the residency apartment had complained about structural safety.

news.title: Nagpur: Builder booked for cheating homebuyers of Rs 12.9 crore
news.para: ​Based on a complaint, the economic offences wing (EOW) of the police has registered a case against Shashank Govindprasad Pandey (46) under sections 406 (criminal breach of trust), 420 (cheating) and other relevant provisions of the Indian Penal Code.

news.title: Compensation, penalties cannot be taxed: Government
news.para: Chartered accountants, tax consultants and taxpayers were grappling over the question whether GST has to be paid for transactions such as liquidated damages, compensation, penalty, cancellation charges, late payment and penalties due to a breach of contract.

news.title: Eight years on, Chandigarh's master plan 2031 still stuck in first gear
news.para: A master plan committee was constituted in December 2009, and after six years of works involving town planning experts and different stakeholders, the CMP was prepared in 2014.

news.title: Fraud alert! Website selling plots near Noida airport site, says YEIDA
news.para: ​It has a similar interface with the official website, with details of YEIDA’s master plan and projects like Noida Airport, Film City, Logistics Hub, among others, and offers a tab/button for registration of plots.

news.title: MSRDB plans to invest over Rs 3,000 crore to expand real estate portfolio in three states
news.para: The company is looking at doubling its retail and commercial portfolio to over 8 mn sq. ft. from 4.5mn sq. ft. it is developing currently.

news.title: IBBI allows bankrupt companies to be split, boost for recovery of due
news.para: The move to split assets is seen to be beneficial in cases involving real estate players and other entities with multiple projects, all of which may not be viable, or there may be some assets which will generate higher value, a senior government official told TOI.

news.title: Avenue Supermarts' CEO buys two flats in Mumbai from Rustomjee for over Rs 66 crore
news.para: The couple has bought these apartments spread over a total 8,379 sq ft from real estate developer Rustomjee Group's subsidiary Keystone Realtors in its project Rustomjee Seasons in Bandra (East) close to the Mumbai's business district of Bandra-Kurla Complex (BKC).

news.title: Now, Rs 4 lakh aid for death at construction site: Haryana CM
news.para: “The financial assistance of Rs 2.5 lakh given to a family in case of death of a construction worker at the workplace will be raised to Rs 4 lakh. Similarly, the financial assistance given to a worker in case of disability due to an accident at the workplace will also be doubled,” the CM said.

news.title: Interest from co-operative bank exempt for housing societies in Mumbai: ITAT
news.para: Co-operative housing societies park their surplus funds with other co-operative entities (that is, banks) and claim tax exemption for the interest under Section 80P of the I-T Act.
